# Comment and Markdown Wrapping

Target ~120 columns from column 0 for all comments and markdown text.

## Rules

- **Target width**: 120 columns measured from column 0 (includes indentation and comment prefixes like `/// `, `// `)
- **Minimum text width**: 80 characters of actual text content, regardless of nesting depth. Even at deep indentation, never cramp text below 80 chars of content — let the line exceed 120 total if needed.
- **Soft wrap**: if the last word pushes slightly past 120 (5-10 chars), keep it rather than creating a one-word orphan on the next line
- **Preserve structure**: never collapse numbered lists, bulleted lists, blank separator lines between sections, or section headers into flowing paragraphs
- **Scope**: `///` XML doc comments, `//` line comments in `.cs` files, and all `.md` files
- **Leave alone**: code lines, `// ──`/`// ══` divider lines, `#pragma` lines, fenced code blocks, table rows, long URLs
